Asian hornets have killed at least six people in France . 
  Experts fear millions of two-inch-long hornets could be heading for Britain . 
  They pose a danger to honeybees and are to be discussed at summit meeting by beekeepers . 
  UK beekeepers have been sent email alerts by Defra to be on the look-out . 
  The hornet is thought to have travelled to France on Chinese pot plants . 
 